🧵 THREAD: I analyzed the comments on the debate: "What is the fastest way to master coding?"

Most advice was generic "just learn the fundamentals" noise.

But User @_newdev0 dropped the specific blueprint you actually need to hear. 👇

1/ The "Project 11" Protocol.

Most "How-To" guides are just procrastination in disguise.

The Truth: Your first 10 projects are supposed to suck. The goal isn't to be perfect. The goal is to survive until the 11th.

2/ Why this works:

You cannot "think" your way to Senior Developer status.

🧠 Theory = False Confidence. 🚢 Shipping = Real Feedback.

Volume negates luck. Stop overthinking and start failing.

3/ The Mindset Shift:

❌ The Old Way: Watch 100 hours of tutorials → Build nothing.
✅ The New Way: Build 10 garbage apps → Fix them → Actually learn.

You can't steer a parked car.

4/ Let's see who is actually shipping.

Drop a link to your "Project 11" (or whatever you are working on right now) in the replies.

I'll check out every single one. 👇
